I was super thrilled to be sent this beautiful @beautifect make up box which has really revolutionised how I do my make up and means I’m no longer tied to my dressing table!✨ 

It comes with a multitude of lighting options, so you can get a super flawless finish whether you’re doing your make up for evening light or heading into the office! 

They really have thought of everything! It even comes with a brilliant little magnifying mirror which is magnetic and clips on to the corner for close up work like ensuring every last eyelash is properly coated with mascara!

There’s lots of room inside to organise your make up, but it’s super practical too as it all wipes clean.  So now I can do my make up on the sofa when I’m watching Netflix or, my personal  favourite on a lazy weekend morning, outside in the garden with a coffee and a croissant listening to the birdsong surrounded by apple blossom! 

PS Yes, it’s a premium product with a premium price, but I did tons of research on @beautifect and it has the most amazing reviews, not just from Vogue and Harpers but also real people like us and I’m now the latest brand fan ✨

Some stills from a very special day at @royalwindsorflowershow - I’ll be sharing a Reel with you soon but there are too many wonderful, wonderful snippets that I needed to share with you (swipe for my conversation with The King - eek!)! 

There are so many reason that @royalwindsorflowershow is my favourite day of the year - quintessentially British, it has the charm of a village fete sprinkled with the unique magic of its royal connections. It harks back to a bygone era of the WI, jam making, sweet peas, Punch & Judy shows and children running a sack race but with stunning garden installations, the oh-so-graceful Duchess of Edinburgh cutting the ribbon to open the show and the Chelsea Pensioners running an egg and spoon race!  And, of course, I adore @alantitchmarshcbe 

As well as truly wonderful horticulture, there is fabulous food, lovely shopping and wonderful performances to enjoy - honestly, if you live anywhere remotely close you must go next year! It will bring you so much joy! 

And it was an incredible honour to meet HRH King Charles III - he was so charismatic and charming - spreading joy and happiness wherever he walked.  He asked me if I’d been to The Royal Windsor Flower Show before, where I have travelled from and what my favourite flower was…..and commented that it was very “tactful” to wear a floral hydrangea dress. 

It is hard to sum up the delights of the @royalwindsorflowershow but suffice to say that it has become an annual tradition for me and I leave with my heart full of joy 🌸 🍃 👑 (and let’s before the divine afternoon tea from @coworthpark 🍰).

Last night was gorgeous - we were still having drinks outside at 9pm, it was so warm! And it was the first night out for my beautiful new Maya Midi Bag from the wonderful @lalage - that pop of orange is everything! It looks amazing with white too…..

If you don’t know @lalage, Lalage launched her eponymously named label in 2004 with years of experience designing for famous English fashion houses such as Mulberry and Burberry. 

Lalage (who is in fact English – her name is ancient Greek and pronounced La - la - ghee) began her career at Aquascutum, where she developed her understanding of the true meaning of quality and this shines out throughout her collection, culminating in her stunning handbag collection which was launched in 2015.

I really can’t emphasise how beautiful the collection is - the soft grainy print Italian calf leather is divine - and it’s lined in contrasting suede and finished with 24 carat gold plate hardware.  I love the subtle branding which exudes discreet luxury and the detachable crossbody strap lends practicality too. 

The Maya really is the perfect luxury handbag and it comes in 14 colours and 3 sizes! Pop into one of their three London stores to see for yourself (Burlington Arcade, Knightsbridge and Belgravia). I’ve linked mine is Stories and my Lalage Highlight ✨

latestPosts.caption:
I haven’t been in to @zara for so, so long but I loved this black two piece - giving me Frankie Shop vibes! 

The linen mix blue dress is a great Summer dress and the belted cream waistcoat is so chic in real life, although I don’t think my content does is justice.

Just wondering, would you like to see more of this type of content? Let me know what labels or shops you’d like to see more of? I keep seeing some great bits on Instagram from @hm too! 

I’ve linked everything in Stories and my May Highlight ✨ 

#zara #frankieshopvibes #highstreetstyle #changingroomselfie #stylediaries #styleover40 #londonblogger #outfitideas

Isn’t this the prettiest polka dot dress from @lalage - it’s totally timeless and so beautiful to style in different ways, as you can bring out all the different colours in the print.

And if you can’t find the perfect hat for your outfit, this idea of creating a fresh flower crown to add to a simple hat, is so pretty from @bloominghaus and why not add a matching corsage for your wrist? 🌸 

For beautiful clothing from @lalage you can view the full collection at their Beauchamp Place showroom - and you can find their truly exceptional collection of luxury handbags also at Burlington Arcade and Lowndes Street. 

PS Love seeing this dress across the years - from 19 to 56!
